title: Feasibility Study — 50 MW Solar Photovoltaic Plant
summary: Al Kharsaah site · NPV / IRR / payback assessment · Recommended for detailed design
meta: | type: feasibility | ref: FS-2026-02 | date: 2026-06-24

section: Executive Summary
text: The proposed 50 MW solar PV plant at Al Kharsaah demonstrates strong financial viability with an NPV of 142M QAR and IRR of 14.2%, exceeding the 12% hurdle rate. The project is recommended for progression to detailed design and EPC tender.

section: Key Performance Indicators
metric: NPV (10-year) | value: 142,000,000 QAR | trend: up | target: 120,000,000 QAR | period: 10 years
metric: IRR | value: 14.2% | target: 12%
metric: Payback Period | value: 6.4 years | target: 8 years
metric: LCOE | value: 0.089 QAR/kWh | trend: down | period: 2026
metric: Capacity Factor | value: 26.5% | target: 25%

section: Assumptions
- Capex: 380,000,000 QAR at 0.90 QAR/Wp installed capacity
- Tariff: 0.18 QAR/kWh fixed for 20 years under PPA
- O&M: 0.015 QAR/kWh escalated at 2% annually
- Degradation: 0.5% per annum
- Debt: 70% at 5.5% interest, 15-year tenor
- Equity: 30% with 12% hurdle rate

section: Financial Model
| Year | Revenue (M QAR) | O&M (M QAR) | EBITDA (M QAR) | DSCR |
| 1 | 69.4 | 5.8 | 63.6 | 1.42 |
| 2 | 69.1 | 5.9 | 63.2 | 1.41 |
| 3 | 68.8 | 6.0 | 62.8 | 1.40 |
| 4 | 68.5 | 6.1 | 62.4 | 1.39 |
| 5 | 68.2 | 6.2 | 62.0 | 1.38 |

section: Risk Assessment
risk: Regulatory change | severity: medium | mitigation: Long-term PPA with government offtaker
risk: Currency fluctuation | severity: low | mitigation: Revenue and debt both in QAR
risk: Grid curtailment | severity: medium | mitigation: Grid impact study completed, 50MW within substation capacity
risk: Module supply chain | severity: high | mitigation: Dual-source procurement strategy, 6-month buffer stock

section: Recommendation
info: Proceed to detailed design phase and initiate EPC tender. | type: success
text: The project clears all financial hurdles and presents acceptable risk profile. Board approval is sought to release Phase 2 budget of 2.5M QAR for detailed engineering.